As a DevOps Engineer,
I want to automatically sync code from a source repository to multiple destination repositories using an Azure DevOps pipeline,
So that I can ensure consistency of code across multiple repositories without manual effort.

1. Pipeline should clone the source repository successfully
2. Pipeline should push code to all configured destination repositories
3. If the feature branch does not exist, it should be created automatically
4. If the branch exists, code should be updated (force push allowed)
5. Pipeline should handle multiple repositories dynamically using a loop
6. Authentication should be handled securely using PAT (variable group)
7. Pipeline should not fail due to existing workspace or repo conflicts
8. Logs should clearly show which repositories were updated
